Though a 
full-service hospital was no longer required, she remained in a
vegetative 
state from which she might never awaken. 
</P>
<P>
Back in Dallas, no sign was posted, but the Raileys' home was quietly
put on 
the market and sold. 
</P>
<P>
Walker Railey voluntarily surrendered his credentials as a minister in
the 
United Methodist Church, and then surrendered control of his wife's
legal 
affairs to her parents. He granted temporary custody of his children to
